speech.blockquote:
“That Seanad Éireann:
noting: - that the 7th of March, 1848, was the day when Thomas F. Meagher raised a Tricolour Flag for the first time, from 33 The Mall in Waterford City;
- that Meagher said of its colours ‘the white in the centre signifies a lasting truce between Orange and Green and I trust that beneath its folds the hands of Irish Protestants and Irish Catholics may be clasped in generous and heroic brotherhood’; in this year, the 150th anniversary of the death of Thomas F. Meagher, formally adopts the protocols and guidelines drawn up by the Department of the Taoiseach for the National Flag.”
